title: Airline industry group slashes its profit forecast as trade war hurts the cargo business
text: IATA Director General and CEO Alexandre de Juniac says trade disputes have hurt international trade, with cargo loads taking the biggest hit.

title: Wall Street Weekahead: Struggles of transport stocks transmit caution to market
text: Add this to worries about Wall Street: The index of planes, trains and trucking companies, considered an important stock barometer of the U.S. economy's health, is struggling.

title: Foxconn halts production lines for Huawei phones, according to reports
text: Huawei, the Chinese technology giant whose devices are at the center of a far-reaching trade dispute between the U.S. and Chinese governments, is reducing orders for new phones, according to a report in The South China Morning Post.

title: Trump's Mexico tariffs slow momentum for North America trade deal
text: Influential business groups fear that Trump's threat against Mexico could derail the proposed trade agreement.

title: The Week Ahead In Biotech: ASCO Presentations Pick Up The Pace
text: Biotech stocks came under pressure this week ahead of the ASCO 2019 presentations.

title: The market's drop in May felt serious, but it is normal for stocks
text: Stocks pulled back sharply in May, battered by trade and economic fears. However, drops like this one are more common than people think.

title: Global airlines slash profit forecast 21% on protectionism fears
text: Global airlines slashed a key industry profit forecast by 21% on Sunday amid concerns over an expanding trade war and higher oil prices.

title: Meet the first private companies that NASA has selected to deliver payloads to the Moon
text: The National Aeronautics and Space Administration has selected Astrobotic, Intuitive Machines, and Orbit Beyond as the first three private companies to deliver science and technology payloads under the Commercial Lunar Payload Services (CLPS) as part of its Artemis program.

title: Meet the billionaires of the new cloud boom
text: From Dropbox's Drew Houston to the lesser-known CEO of Paycom, the booming cloud software market has created a number of billionaires.

title: Measuring Carbon Emissions From Space Will Help Bring Pollution Back Down To Earth
text: A new initiative, backed by Google's AI Impact Challenge, will combine satellite data and artificial intelligence to track carbon emissions around the world, and make the information available to everyone.

title: Everyone still relies on a stock's P-E ratio to invest, but a study shows it's bunk
text: Evaluating the price-to-earnings ratio is a deeply ingrained practice for investors. But it isn't a metric that delivers positive results.

title: Can't get to Galaxy's Edge? Here are 10 Star Wars worlds you can visit right here on Earth
text: Over the course of 10 movies and four decades, "Star Wars" has been filmed in dozens of countries from Tunisia to the Maldives. Here are 10 planets and moons you can visit without having to rev up your hyperdrive.

title: Weak Consumer Spending And Trade War Madness Fuel 2020 Recession Chances
text: The trade war is not the only concern for the U.S. economy. The consumer has been retreating for some time, industrial production is weakening, and fixed investment is not accelerating as expected in the wake of massive deregulation and tax cuts.

title: Stocks To Watch: Apple's WWDC, DuPont's Return And Tariff Anxiety
text: Welcome to Seeking Alpha's Stocks to Watch - a preview of key events scheduled for the next week.

title: Budget airlines the flavor of South Korean aviation market, Jeju travel booms
text: Kim Bo-Min, a Starbucks barista, paid 140,000 won ($118) for a round-trip from her hometown of Daegu to the popular resort island of Jeju, arriving on T'Way Air Co Ltd, part of South Korea's rapidly growing low-cost airline sector.
